  "texts": [
    "These methods typically struggle to accurately position body parts such as the arms and hands, resulting in unrealistic, less immersive experiences for users.",
    "Additionally, segmentation-based approaches, such as Viton-HD [5] and ACGPN [32], encounter difficulties, particularly in filling misaligned regions with proper clothing textures.",
    "Their heavy reliance on accurate human parsing means that even minor errors in segmentation can result in significant artifacts, which degrade the overall quality of the generated images.",
    "While parser-free methods aim to simplify the try-on process by eliminating the need for detailed human parsing, they introduce their own set of challenges.",
    "These methods often struggle with artifacts arising from repetitively using the same input-output pairs during training."
  ],
